00:00:01.291 --> 00:00:03.540
ROB PASKOWSKI: Well, thanks
everyone for coming today.

00:00:03.540 --> 00:00:04.310
Good afternoon.

00:00:04.310 --> 00:00:07.550
My name is Rob Paskowski, and
I'm on the Google benefits team

00:00:07.550 --> 00:00:09.780
here in Sunnyvale, California.

00:00:09.780 --> 00:00:13.780
And I focus on managing our
Google US health care strategy.

00:00:13.780 --> 00:00:15.280
The team sponsoring
this event asked

00:00:15.280 --> 00:00:18.000
me to speak because of my
experience as a benefits

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:20.500
professional, as a leader in
the Google People Operations,

00:00:20.500 --> 00:00:23.620
but also, being a dad
and being an autism dad.

00:00:23.620 --> 00:00:28.140
So a father to nine-year-old
son with autism.

00:00:28.140 --> 00:00:31.300
So you see, my journey
as a People Operations

00:00:31.300 --> 00:00:32.800
guy, a benefits
professional, really

00:00:32.800 --> 00:00:36.550
did change in 2009 when my
son was diagnosed with autism.

00:00:36.550 --> 00:00:40.530
And quickly after the shock
and everything that goes,

00:00:40.530 --> 00:00:44.860
the emotions that go into
that, after helping my son get

00:00:44.860 --> 00:00:47.640
the services he needed
and everything like that,

00:00:47.640 --> 00:00:52.470
I quickly realised that there
was a gap in the services

00:00:52.470 --> 00:00:55.460
provided to parents who
have special needs children,

00:00:55.460 --> 00:00:58.970
both in therapy and benefits,
but also in leave programs.

00:00:58.970 --> 00:01:01.810
So I had set out on
a journey, and this

00:01:01.810 --> 00:01:04.220
parallels some of
the work that Josh is

00:01:04.220 --> 00:01:06.290
doing around parental benefits.

00:01:06.290 --> 00:01:08.740
But I set out on my own
journey at that point

00:01:08.740 --> 00:01:12.580
to see how can we help other
special needs families deal

00:01:12.580 --> 00:01:14.950
with this dilemma, whether
it's coverage for therapy,

00:01:14.950 --> 00:01:17.710
or leave benefits,
and things like that.

00:01:17.710 --> 00:01:21.190
So I set out on a mission
to develop an autism support

00:01:21.190 --> 00:01:24.040
program and benefits program for
the company I was working out

00:01:24.040 --> 00:01:25.140
at the time.

00:01:25.140 --> 00:01:27.470
And it worked, out worked
with consultants, worked

00:01:27.470 --> 00:01:30.754
with the autism advocacy
groups, and with the insurance

00:01:30.754 --> 00:01:32.545
carriers, as well to
put something together

00:01:32.545 --> 00:01:34.044
that could really
work for families.

00:01:34.044 --> 00:01:35.840
So we put in something
I was really, really

00:01:35.840 --> 00:01:38.840
proud of, but then
realized that hey,

00:01:38.840 --> 00:01:40.420
this was just one organization.

00:01:40.420 --> 00:01:42.010
How can we really
change the culture

00:01:42.010 --> 00:01:45.590
around how we support
parents in this little niche

00:01:45.590 --> 00:01:46.765
around special needs?

00:01:46.765 --> 00:01:48.890
And then I started working
with the advocacy groups

00:01:48.890 --> 00:01:51.880
to do with more employers;
so get more employers

00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:53.720
to understand,
hearing it from a dad,

00:01:53.720 --> 00:01:55.630
but also from a
benefits professional

00:01:55.630 --> 00:01:57.956
that I could speak the
same language to them

00:01:57.956 --> 00:01:59.580
and help them set up
their own program.

00:01:59.580 --> 00:02:03.380
So I was able to scale that
and help over a dozen companies

00:02:03.380 --> 00:02:05.760
implement comprehensive
autism support

00:02:05.760 --> 00:02:08.336
programs that leave benefits
to support their employees.

00:02:08.336 --> 00:02:10.169
And I have spoken at a
number of conferences

00:02:10.169 --> 00:02:12.680
to help others just
dispel the myths

00:02:12.680 --> 00:02:14.730
and really get the
true information out

00:02:14.730 --> 00:02:17.890
there about how they can
really help their families.

00:02:17.890 --> 00:02:20.090
And the results have been
amazing that you just

00:02:20.090 --> 00:02:21.450
have more loyal employees.

00:02:21.450 --> 00:02:23.220
There's a business
value to all the things

00:02:23.220 --> 00:02:24.180
